Elena and Fernando's son, Miguel.

202
00:14:45,053 --> 00:14:46,596
Can we talk about that?

203
00:14:46,679 --> 00:14:48,973
What was his condition?
Miguel's condition?

204
00:14:49,724 --> 00:14:51,350
He had what's called Wilms tumor.

205
00:14:51,434 --> 00:14:53,394
It's cancer of the kidney.

206
00:14:53,478 --> 00:14:57,482
Most common among children,
and Miguel bore that statistical brunt.

207
00:14:57,565 --> 00:14:58,858
What was his treatment?

208
00:14:58,941 --> 00:15:01,778
He was unlucky
in that normal medical practice had failed.

209
00:15:01,861 --> 00:15:02,861
I...

210
00:15:04,655 --> 00:15:05,948
used to lead a team

211
00:15:06,657 --> 00:15:11,245
that specialized in a procedure called
autologous bone marrow transplant.

212
00:15:11,829 --> 00:15:14,499
It's a long and relatively new process,

213
00:15:14,582 --> 00:15:17,585
but happily, it was entirely successful
in Miguel's case.

214
00:15:17,668 --> 00:15:20,713
By the end, we'd all become quite close.
Cancer can do that.

215
00:15:21,380 --> 00:15:23,382
There's been much discussion of...

216
00:15:24,425 --> 00:15:27,595
