217
00:15:29,847 --> 00:15:31,224
But I also quite love him.

218
00:15:31,933 --> 00:15:33,059
Miguel.

219
00:15:33,142 --> 00:15:36,687
Yeah, he became like a son,
which is not advisable.

220
00:15:37,814 --> 00:15:41,734
Um... pediatric oncologists
becoming too close to their patients...

221
00:15:42,401 --> 00:15:44,529
well, it's a recipe for depression,

222
00:15:44,612 --> 00:15:47,156
if not utter personal doom,

223
00:15:47,240 --> 00:15:50,201
but, uh, I found I had no choice
more times than not.

224
00:15:50,284 --> 00:15:53,621
And I certainly had no choice with Miguel.
He's...

225
00:15:54,247 --> 00:15:56,124
<i>He's a remarkable young man.</i>

226
00:15:57,708 --> 00:15:59,669
<i>You keep calling him a man.</i>

227
00:16:01,212 --> 00:16:02,880
Yeah, he's a young boy.

228
00:16:03,464 --> 00:16:05,967
But to fight the cancer he did,

229
00:16:07,301 --> 00:16:08,928
with the ferocity he showed,

230
00:16:10,513 --> 00:16:11,931
and the good humor,

231
00:16:13,182 --> 00:16:15,143
there's a man in there, I assure you.

232
00:16:17,520 --> 00:16:20,106
After the surgery,
during chemotherapy,

233
00:16:20,606 --> 00:16:22,608
you often slept in his hospital room.

234
00:16:22,692 --> 00:16:25,236
Well, as I say, I'd become very attached.

235
00:16:25,319 --> 00:16:28,281
There were some touch-and-go moments,
and I wasn't gonna lose him.

236
00:16:29,532 --> 00:16:31,117
I was very determined about that.

237
00:16:33,452 --> 00:16:34,452
Um...

238
00:16:34,829 --> 00:16:36,664
Another reason, of course, why...

239
00:16:40,126 --> 00:16:41,377
Another reason what?

240
00:16:44,005 --> 00:16:45,298
Well, he was like a son.

241
00:16:46,757 --> 00:16:48,426
What was done to his mother...

242
00:16:57,101 --> 00:16:58,519
I could never do such a thing.

243
00:16:58,603 --> 00:17:01,022
Not to her, and not to him.

244
00:17:05,818 --> 00:17:06,861
Thank you.

245
00:17:19,582 --> 00:17:22,585
You discovered Miguel's mother
like this.

246
00:17:23,628 --> 00:17:24,628
I did, yeah.

247
00:17:25,171 --> 00:17:27,715
And when the police found her
the next morning,

248
00:17:27,798 --> 00:17:30,384
when they came looking
to ask you questions,

249
00:17:30,968 --> 00:17:31,969
uh, where were you then?

250
00:17:34,555 --> 00:17:37,141
Near Lake George,
upstate New York, in a motel.

251
00:17:37,808 --> 00:17:39,936
- How'd you get there?
- I drove.

252
00:17:40,603 --> 00:17:41,603
Hmm.

253
00:17:50,154 --> 00:17:52,573
You say you loved Elena Alves.

254
00:17:52,657 --> 00:17:55,201
- Yeah.
- You discovered her like this.

255
00:17:56,452 --> 00:17:58,913
May I ask you to look
at the screen, please?

256
00:18:00,748 --> 00:18:01,749
Sir?

257
